title: Potrait Photography
description: Portrait photography is a very well-known and popular style of photography. This style of photography is all about trying to capture the personality, identity, soul, and emotions of a person by utilizing the background atmosphere, poses, and lighting.

title: Wedding Photography
description: Wedding photography is a specialty in photography that is primarily focused on the photography of events and activities relating to weddings.

title: Pre-Wedding Photography
description: A pre-shoot is a short photo session with your wedding photographer approximately three to six months before your wedding. The main aim of the pre-shoot is to get used to being in front of the camera, build rapport with your photographer, and receive a lovely set of romantic photographs well before your wedding.

title: Post-Wedding Photography
description: An after session, or often called a post-wedding session, is exactly how it sounds. A photoshoot after you’re already married. This can be the day after you tie the knot, a few weeks, or even years after your marriage. Simply put, it’s a chance for you to slip back into your wedding dress and suit, get your hair and makeup done again, and have a full romantic photo session celebrating your love.

title: Fashion Photography
description: A fashion photographer takes photographs of the latest clothes, accessories, hairstyles and make-up. Save. Share. Fashion photographers are responsible for how clothing is presented in advertising campaigns, catalogues and fashion magazines.

title: Product Photography
description: Product photography, or e-commerce photography as it's sometimes known, is basically what it sounds like: photos taken and used on websites and social media platforms to help drive sales of your product or service.
